## Section 10: TextField Component

### 10.1 Component Overview

**Description**: A versatile text input field component with label, helper text, error states, and icon support. Includes glassmorphic styling for SabPaisa's design language.

**Location**: `src/components/ui/TextField.tsx`

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Single-line text input (name, email, phone, etc.)
- ✅ Forms requiring user input
- ✅ Search fields

**When NOT to Use**:
- ❌ Multi-line text → Use `<TextArea>`
- ❌ Selecting from options → Use `<Select>` or `<Dropdown>`
- ❌ Numeric-only input → Use `<NumberInput>`
- ❌ Date/time → Use `<DatePicker>`

---

### 10.2 TypeScript Interface

```typescript
interface TextFieldProps extends React.InputHTMLAttributes<HTMLInputElement> {
  /** Field name (required for forms) */
  name: string;

  /** Label displayed above input */
  label?: string;

  /** Helper text displayed below input */
  helperText?: string;

  /** Icon displayed on the left side */
  leftIcon?: React.ReactNode;

  /** Icon displayed on the right side */
  rightIcon?: React.ReactNode;

  /** Visual style variant */
  variant?: 'default' | 'filled' | 'outlined';

  /** Error state (controlled externally) */
  error?: boolean;

  /** Error message to display */
  errorMessage?: string;

  /** All standard HTML input attributes */
  type?: string;
  placeholder?: string;
  value?: string;
  onChange?: React.ChangeEventHandler<HTMLInputElement>;
  required?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
  readOnly?: boolean;
  autoComplete?: string;
  autoFocus?: boolean;
  maxLength?: number;
  pattern?: string;
}
```

---

### 10.3 All Variants (3 Variants)

#### Variant: Default

**Visual Specs**:
- Background: `bg-white/10` with `backdrop-blur-sm`
- Border: `border border-white/20` → `hover:border-white/30`
- Focus: `focus:border-blue-400` + `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-400/50`
- Text: White
- Placeholder: `placeholder-white/50`

**CSS Classes**:
```css
bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/20
rounded-xl focus:ring-blue-400/50 focus:border-blue-400
hover:border-white/30 text-white placeholder-white/50
```

**When to Use**:
- ✅ **Standard input fields (DEFAULT)**
- ✅ Most form fields

**Code Example**:
```tsx
<TextField
  name="email"
  label="Email Address"
  type="email"
  placeholder="you@example.com"
  required
/>
```

---

#### Variant: Filled

**Visual Specs**:
- Background: `bg-white/10` → `focus:bg-white/15`
- Border: `border-transparent` → `focus:border-blue-400`
- More subtle than default

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Dense forms with many fields
- ✅ When subtle styling is preferred

---

#### Variant: Outlined

**Visual Specs**:
- Border: `border-2 border-white/20` (thicker border)
- Background: `bg-white/10`
- More prominent border

**When to Use**:
- ✅ When field needs more emphasis
- ✅ Single prominent input (like search)

---

### 10.4 All States

#### State: Default
- Border: `border-white/20`
- Background: `bg-white/10`
- Text: `text-white`

#### State: Hover
- Border: `border-white/30` (increased opacity)

#### State: Focus
- Border: `border-blue-400` (solid blue)
- Ring: `ring-2 ring-blue-400/50` (glow effect)
- Background: Slight brightness increase

#### State: Filled (Has Value)
- No visual change (same as default)
- Text displayed in white

#### State: Error
- Border: `border-red-400`
- Focus Ring: `ring-red-400/50`
- Error message shown below in `text-red-400`

**Code**:
```tsx
<TextField
  name="pan"
  label="PAN Number"
  error={true}
  errorMessage="Invalid PAN format. Expected: ABCDE1234F"
/>
```

#### State: Disabled
- Opacity: `opacity-50`
- Cursor: `cursor-not-allowed`
- Non-interactive

**Code**:
```tsx
<TextField
  name="merchantCode"
  label="Merchant Code"
  value="MERCH001"
  disabled
/>
```

#### State: Read-Only
- Similar styling to disabled but with full opacity
- Allows text selection and copying

**Code**:
```tsx
<TextField
  name="transactionId"
  label="Transaction ID"
  value="TXN20250115000123"
  readOnly
  rightIcon={<Copy className="cursor-pointer" onClick={handleCopy} />}
/>
```

---

### 10.5 Code Examples

#### Example 1: Basic Text Input

```tsx
import TextField from '@/components/ui/TextField';

<TextField
  name="fullName"
  label="Full Name"
  placeholder="Enter your full name"
  required
  helperText="As per your official documents"
/>
```

---

#### Example 2: Email Input with Validation

```tsx
